<plot>Jack is a man who can take no more. With more opinions than a room full of politicians he's about to take us into his world. Dismayed at the lack of morality in the world, Jack shows us first hand how he proposes the ameliorate the problem. Using the contrivance of a night out at the local strip club he pulls three of his acquaintances into a deadly game of confession, highlighting why they are all morally repugnant. The following day Jack removes them from the equation of society... posing the question: is he right or wrong in his extreme actions?</plot><url>http://localhost:8983/solr/movie.html?272060</url></doc>
